<p>The state's solar industry has experienced explosive growth, climbing from virtually no solar capacity in 2010 to over 7,000 MW of installed capacity by 2023, ranking North Carolina as the 4th largest solar state in the nation. This rapid expansion has created a competitive marketplace with numerous qualified installers, driving down costs while improving installation quality and customer service. Most residential solar systems in North Carolina are grid-tied installations that take advantage of Duke Energy's net metering program, allowing homeowners to receive credit for excess electricity generated during peak sun hours and consumed during evening hours or cloudy days.</p>

